The paper discusses Oblivious Shuffling and K-Oblivious Shuffling, which are cryptographic protocols for secure data shuffling. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The algorithms presented also involve data structures and algorithms for efficient shuffling, which could be classified under data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses bandwidth usage and storage requirements, which could be classified under information theory (cs.IT) and computer architecture (cs.CC).
